article.headline: Stetson 57, Campbell 52
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. (AP) -- Garfield Blair scored 17 points to lead Stetson to a 57-52 victory against Campbell on Saturday. A.J. Smith added 14 points for the Hatters (10-11, 5-2 Atlantic Sun), who forced 24 turnovers and turned them into 19 points in bouncing back from a loss at Gardner-Webb that ended a five-game winning streak. Stetson held the Atlantic Sun's leading scorer, Campbell's Jonathan Rodriguez, to 11 points -- more than 10 fewer than his average of 21.8. He was just 3 of 11 from the field. Reggie Bishop had 21 points to lead the Camels (8-11, 3-4), who shot 38 percent, held the Hatters to 34 percent shooting and claimed a 37-34 rebounding advantage.
